This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with instance segmentation in biological images. The use of integer programming and column generation also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of optimization techniques such as odd set inequalities suggests that it could belong to the discrete mathematics (cs.DS) sub-category. Finally, the use of neural networks for cell detection and segmentation could also suggest that it could belong to the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category.
